          {
            "type": "text",
            "id": "1f4cc846-be94-4cab-9091-db3180c188a0",
            "text": {
              "ops": [
                {
                  "insert": "Health & Behavior Monitoring",
                  "attributes": {
                    "bold": true
                  }
                },
                {
                  "insert": " 7.1. "
                },
                {
                  "insert": "Daily Health Check",
                  "attributes": {
                    "bold": true
                  }
                },
                {
                  "insert": " (during morning and evening care) - Observe: - Appetite (ate full meal, partial, or refused). - Stool quality (normal, loose, diarrhea, presence of blood). - Energy level (normal, lethargic, unusually hyper). - Any limping, coughing, sneezing, or signs of discomfort. - Document findings in his log. 7.2. "
                },
                {
                  "insert": "Behavior Observations",
                  "attributes": {
                    "bold": true
                  }
                },
                {
                  "insert": " - Note changes in: - Sociability with humans or dogs. - Reactivity, anxiety, or signs of stress (pacing, whining, hiding, excessive panting). - Report concerning changes to the supervisor promptly."
                },
                {
                  "insert": "\n",
                  "attributes": {
                    "paragraph": true
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            "format": {
              "node": "number",
              "children": "number"
            },
            "collapsed": false,
            "completed": false,
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "id": "c656b9e2-dabb-423a-a4b0-5c7aac67171e",
            "text": {
              "ops": [
                {
                  "insert": "Emergency & Incident Protocols",
                  "attributes": {
                    "bold": true
                  }
                },
                {
                  "insert": " 8.1. "
                },
                {
                  "insert": "Medical Emergency (injury, collapse, severe distress)",
                  "attributes": {
                    "bold": true
                  }
                },
                {
                  "insert": " - Immediately notify "
                },
                {
                  "insert": "shift supervisor or manager",
                  "attributes": {
                    "bold": true
                  }
                },
                {
                  "insert": ". - Follow facility "
                },
                {
                  "insert": "veterinary emergency protocol",
                  "attributes": {
                    "bold": true
                  }
                },
                {
                  "insert": " (designated vet/ER). - Once stabilized and per facility policy, contact: - "
                },
                {
                  "insert": "Owner/Emergency Contact: Michael Mitchell – +1 (555) 876-5432",
                  "attributes": {
                    "bold": true
                  }
                },
                {
                  "insert": ". - Document the incident with "
                },
                {
                  "insert": "time, nature of issue, actions taken, and outcomes",
                  "attributes": {
                    "bold": true
                  }
                },
                {
                  "insert": ". 8.2. "
                },
                {
                  "insert": "Behavioral Incident",
                  "attributes": {
                    "bold": true
                  }
                },
                {
                  "insert": " (dog fight, bite, escape attempt) - Safely separate animals using approved methods (distraction, barriers; avoid putting hands between dogs). - Move Charlie to a "
                },
                {
                  "insert": "quiet, secure area",
                  "attributes": {
                    "bold": true
                  }
                },
                {
                  "insert": " and assess for injuries. - Inform supervisor immediately. - Record details: triggers, participants, location, time, and any injuries. - Supervisor/management to determine if owner contact is required."
                },
                {
                  "insert": "\n",
                  "attributes": {
                    "paragraph": true
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            "format": {
              "node": "number",
              "children": "number"
            },
